Summary:¶

Parameters:

  • no iterations: 20
  • iteration runtime limit: 105s
  • population size: 20
  • operator 2 repair heuristic: greedy regret heuristic
    • k regret: 2
    • regret weight: [0.5, 0.5]

No premature convergence was observed. For the comparison, results are merged with the ones from the previous labs (lab-6 and lab-7). While Hybrid Evolution Methods have scored worse than Local Search LSN (no LS) and on par with Local Search Iterative (no LS) in terms of the best solution found, their average score is much better. In TSPC within Hybrid Evolution Methods, the best results were achieved by HAE Operator 2 (LS) with others performing worse within range of 1000 in both average and best score. In TSPD while retaining similar order of results (with exception of Operator 2 (no LS) amd Operator 1 (LS)), difference in scores widens to range of up to 3000 with relation to Operator 2 (LS).
